  id: Clavicular_intersection.L
  partName: Clavicular intersection Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left clavicular intersection represents the anatomical region where clavicular
    structures and associated connective tissues interact within the canine shoulder
    area. Although dogs possess a reduced clavicle compared to humans, this region
    still serves as an important site for muscular attachment and forelimb stabilization.
  - It contributes to maintaining proper spacing and movement between the scapula
    and thoracic wall during locomotion. Surrounding muscles and ligaments coordinate
    through this area to facilitate efficient shoulder mechanics, flexibility, and
    limb control. Proper structural integrity supports balanced forelimb motion and
    shock absorption during activity.
